article.headline: Charleston Southern 61, The Citadel 60
article.story: CHARLESTON, S.C. -- Jamarco Warren scored with 1.2 seconds left in the game to lift Charleston Southern to a 61-60 victory over The Citadel on Tuesday night. Warren drove the lane to score and finished with 13 points, going 6-for-9 from the field. The Bulldogs called a time out but couldn't get a final shot. There were eight ties and 10 lead changes. Kelvin Martin led Charleston Southern (1-1) with 15 points and 10 rebounds. Joe Wolfinger hit a jumper to give The Citadel a 60-57 lead with 1:58 remaining. Jeremy Sexton's jumper cut the lead to 60-59 with 1:30 left and Wolfinger missed a shot to set up Warren's heroics. Cameron Wells led the Citadel (1-1) with 23 points. Zach Urbanus scored 12 points and Wolfinger added 10 points to go with nine rebounds. Charleston Southern was 25-for-48 from the field (52.1 percent) and survived despite making 20 turnovers.
